  "prompt": "What are the steps that I can take to stop marriage hall nuisance operating next to my house causing too much sound from music and chattering etc?",
  "response": "Here are several steps you can take to address the marriage hall nuisance:\n\n1. Initial Communication\n- Directly speak with marriage hall management\n- Politely explain the noise disturbance\n- Request reduced sound levels or better sound insulation\n\n2. Local Administrative Measures\n- Contact local municipal corporation\n- File a complaint about noise pollution\n- Request inspection of venue's noise levels\n\n3. Legal Options\n- Check local noise pollution regulations\n- Verify if marriage hall has necessary permissions\n- Consult local police about noise ordinances\n\n4. Documentation\n- Record noise levels using decibel meter\n- Keep audio/video evidence\n- Maintain a log of disturbances with dates/times\n\n5. Formal Complaints\n- Submit written complaint to:\n- Local police station\n- Municipal corporation\n- Pollution control board\n- Local noise pollution authorities\n\n6. Legal Remedies\n- Seek legal advice\n- Consider filing a civil suit\n- Explore injunction against excessive noise\n\n7. Government Helplines\n- Contact state pollution control helplines\n- Use online grievance redressal platforms\n\n8. Community Support\n- Discuss issue with neighboring residents\n- Collectively approach authorities\n- Create group representation\n\n9. Alternative Dispute Resolution\n- Consider mediation\n- Seek intervention from local leaders\n\nRemember to remain calm and follow legal procedures systematically.",
